Quite obvious if you look at it closely, but some explanation should be given anyway.

The program consists of 3 parts:

    |                |        |                 |
    | `````````````` | ENGINE |      DATA       |
    |                |        |                 |
    |      2N+2      |    N   |      2N+2       |

<code>ENGINE</code> is a function of length N that accepts pairs of boolean arguments:

* It accumulates the list of {𝟙,𝟚,𝟛} codes and counts number of pairs given.
* If {FALSE, FALSE} is given, it adds 𝟛 to the front of the list and two 𝟛's to the end, then it calls itself recursively to accept next pair of boolens.
* If {FALSE, TRUE} is given, it adds 𝟙 to the front of the list and (𝟛,𝟙) to the end, then it calls itself recursively.
* If {TRUE, FALSE} is given, it adds 𝟚 to the front of the list and (𝟙,𝟛) to the end, then it calls itself recursively.
* If (TRUE, TRUE} is given, it adds (2N+2) 𝟚's to the front of the list and two 𝟙's to the end, then the list is printed.

We use alternative boolean implementation (with the shortest possible representation of boolean constants but with longer "if" operator):

    true = I
    false = J
    COND I I (λ garbage . THEN-BRANCH) (λ garbage . ELSE-BRANCH)

What are 𝟙, 𝟚 and 𝟛? They are Q<sub>1</sub>, Q<sub>2</sub> and Q<sub>4</sub> combinators:

    Q<sub>1</sub> = λ x y z . x (z y)
    Q<sub>2</sub> = λ x y z . y (z x)
    Q<sub>4</sub> = λ x y z . z (y x)

Such a choice allows to do this:

    value (λ garbage . <print 'i'>)
          (λ garbage . <print '`'>)
          (λ garbage . <print 'j'>)

----

Okay, that's what <code>ENGINE</code> does. Where's the QUINE?

Let's look at the outputs of this program:

    PROG:   ```````` <ENGINE> jjjiijii
    OUTPUT: `````````ijjjjiijii

PROG's output consists of 3 parts:

* Sequence of <code>`</code> characters. The length of the sequence is the same as the length of <code>DATA</code> section.
* Decoded <code>DATA</code> in reverse order. "Decoded" means:
** <code>ij</code> becomes <code>`</code>
** <code>ji</code> becomes <code>i</code>
** <code>jj</code> becomes <code>j</code>

    ```````` `ij jj ji ij ii
             ^^^ ~~ ~~ ~~ ~~
             |||_/  /  /  |
             ||____/  /   |
             |_______/   STOP

* Copy of <code>DATA</code> section.
What <code>DATA</code> should we pass to the <code>ENGINE</code> to make QUINE? It must be encoded <code>ENGINE</code> reversed!

